author: Content Writer Isha
title: अस्पताल में जा रही एंबुलेंस को कार ने मारी जोरदारी टक्कर, पलटते हुए बजी दीवार में... 4 लोग हुए घायल - a car hit an ambulance going to the hospital-mobile
text:
अस्पताल में जा रही एंबुलेंस को कार ने मारी जोरदारी टक्कर, पलटते हुए बजी दीवार में... 4 लोग हुए घायल
punjabkesari.in Thursday, Jul 03, 2025 - 09:10 AM (IST)
यमुनानगर (परवेज खान): यमुनानगर सिविल अस्पताल गेट के सामने आज सुबह तड़के 4 बजे एक भीषण सड़क हादसा हुआ। छछरौली की तरफ से आ रही तेज रफ्तार कार ने सिविल अस्पताल के गेट के अंदर जा रही एंबुलेंस को ऐसी जोरदार टक्कर मारी की कार पलटते हुए अस्पताल की दीवार से जा टकराई और एंबुलेंस एम्बुलेंस में जा भिड़ी।
एंबुलेंस गर्भवती महिला को यमुनानगर के गांधीनगर से सिविल अस्पताल लेकर आ रही थी। इस हादसे में कार का ड्राइवर गंभीर रूप से जख्मी हुआ है जिसे यमुनानगर के सिविल अस्पताल में भर्ती कराने के बाद चंडीगढ़ पीजीआई रेफर कर दिया है इसके अलावा एंबुलेंस का ड्राइवर भी बुरी तरह से जख्मी हुआ है इस हादसे में तीन लोगों को चोटे आई है हादसे के बाद डायल 112 की गाड़ी मौके पर पहुंची और घायलों को अस्पताल में भर्ती कराया।
घायल एंबुलेंस ड्राइवर सतीश ने बताया कि कार काफी तेज गति से आ रही थी कार में चार लोग सवार थे। जो अपना नियंत्रण खो चुके थे जिससे ये हादसा हुआ है। डायल 112 के पुलिसकर्मी मोहन ने बताया कि फिलहाल यह तफ्तीश का विषय है कि कार सवार युवकों ने शराब पी थी या नहीं लेकिन इस हादसे में चार लोगों को चोटे आई हैं जिनका इलाज कराया जा रहा है। एम्बुलेंस में सवार गर्भवती महिला सुरक्षित है जबकि उनके परिजनों को चोट लगी है।

author: Rob Oesterle
title: Meet the 2023-24 Herald-News Girls Wrestling All-Area Team
text: Here is the 2023-24 Herald-News All-Area Girls Wrestling Team. FIRST TEAM Addison Calteaux, Minooka: Calteaux, a sophomore, finished fourth at 130 at the state finals for the [Indians](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/minooka-preps/). She ended the season with a 27-6 record. Kiernan Farmer, Peotone: Farmer, a senior, won the state championship at 170 for the [Blue Devils](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/peotone-preps/). She finished the season with a record of 21-1. Gracie Guarino, Lincoln-Way Central: Guarino, a senior, took third at 115 for the [Knights](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/lincoln-way-central-preps/). She is a three-time state medalist after taking second at 120 the previous two seasons. She ended her season with a record of 27-1. Claudia Heeney, Lockport: Heeney, a sophomore, won the 130-pound state championship for the [Porters](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/lockport-preps/) with a 4-2 decision over Collinsville’s Taylor Dawson. She finished her season with a 21-1 record despite missing five weeks because of a broken thumb. Eliana Paramo, Joliet Township: Paramo, a senior, won her third state medal for the [Steelmen](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/joliet-central-preps/), finishing second at 110 to Lockport’s Morgan Turner. She finished her season with a recored of 37-4. Katie Ramirez-Quintero, Bolingbrook: Ramirez-Quintero, a senior, won her second state medal by taking third at 135 for the [Raiders](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/bolingbrook-preps/). She ended her season with a record of 34-4. Alicia Tucker, Plainfield Central: Tucker, a junior, finished second at 170 after winning the state title at 155 last season for the [Wildcats](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/plainfield-central-preps/). She finished her season with a record of 36-2 with both losses coming to state champion Kiernan Farmer of Peotone. Morgan Turner, Lockport: Turner, a sophomore, won the 110-pound state championship after becoming the first girl to win a medal at the state boys tournament last year while attending Bremen. Turner spent most of the season wrestling for the Porters’ boys team and finished with a record of 11-0 in girls matches. HONORABLE MENTION Teagan Aurich, [Plainfield South](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/plainfield-south-preps/); Eva Beck, Minooka; Izabel Barrera, Joliet Township: Cheya Bishop, [Joliet Catholic Academy](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/joliet-catholic-preps/); Averi Colella, Lockport; Morgan Congo, [Morris](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/morris-preps/); Zoe Dempsey, [Lincoln-Way West](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/lincoln-way-west-preps/); Sammie Griesen, [Seneca](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/seneca-preps/); Peyton Kueltzo, Minooka; Grace Laird, Joliet Catholic Academy; Ella McDonnell, Morris; Rebekah Ramirez, Lockport; Henessis Villagrama, [Romeoville](https://www.shawlocal.com/tags/romeoville-preps/).

author: Awin P
title: Ben Stokes hits back at Harmison's remarks of England losing 5-0 against India
text: New Delhi, December 28 E ngland Test skipper Ben Stokes hit back at former cricketer Steve Harmison for his remarks on England's lack of preparation for their upcoming Test series against India. ngland Test skipper Ben Stokes hit back at former cricketer Steve Harmison for his remarks on England's lack of preparation for their upcoming Test series against India. Former pacer Harmison who is also a close friend of Stokes questioned England arriving in India just three days before the five-match Test series. He feels that the lack of acclimation could turn out to be a recipe for disaster. He also went on to claim that England could go on to "deserve to get beaten 5-0". Stokes replied to a video of Harmison's comments and said as quoted from Sky Sports, "Good job we're going to Abu Dhabi for a training camp before we go to India for even more training before that first Test then, isn't it?" Harmison suggested that England's approach regarding their Test series against India was insufficient while telling talkSPORT as quoted from Sky Sports, "If England go in three days before, they deserve to get beat 5-0, they really do." "I'm an old man, that's what they'll say. Times have changed, but preparation hasn't changed. I love this new approach, I love Ben Stokes and [head coach] Brendon McCullum. But I'm sorry, going three days before... You'd never do that for an Ashes series. You'd never go to Australia three days before the Gabba, so why go three days before Hyderabad? For me it stinks, it absolutely stinks," Harmison added. England would be keen to turn their fortunes around in 2024 as last time they lost 3-1 on Indian soil. Meanwhile, Stokes is in a race against time to get fit for the series. The experienced all-rounder had recently come out of ODI retirement to participate in the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023, where he played as a specialist batter. His issues with his knee have prevented him from playing his role as an all-rounder effectively as he has rarely bowled as of late. He went for knee surgery after the World Cup which was successful and now it is time for him to undergo rehabilitation. author: Jordy McElroy
title: Report: WR Kayshon Boutte arrested on illegal online gaming charges
text:
New England Patriots rookie wide receiver Kayshon Boutte has reportedly been arrested on illegal online gaming charges. WAFB 9 reported the news on Thursday.
Per the report, some of the alleged illegal gaming occurred when Boutte was still in college at LSU. He is accused of creating a fake account representing himself as 21 years old or older, despite being underaged for gambling.
This enabled him to place “thousands of different bets including some on LSU football” with “several hundred thousand dollars” in wagers and payouts.
Boutte has since turned himself in with one misdemeanor charge and a felony. He was set to be booked at East Baton Rouge Parish Prison and be released after posting $6,000 bond.
There was a time when Boutte was believed to be one of the best receiving prospects in the country, but he ultimately fell to the Patriots in the sixth-round of the 2023 NFL draft. He failed to make an impact in his first year with only five game appearances and two receptions for 19 yards.
Per WAFB 9, through a source, Boutte “never bet ‘against himself'” and isn’t being accused of throwing games in college.

author: Belén Zapata
title: Tortilla y Alegría junto con sus cachorros no pierden la esperanza de ser adoptados
text:
Tortilla y Alegría, quien tiene seis cachorros, viven en distintas ciudades, pero comparten un aspecto: ambas fueron abandonadas con sus bebés.
En el caso de Tortilla la salvó el hogar de acogida Salvavidas en Cuenca y con Alegría, refugio Pana, en Guayaquil. El deseo de todos es que lleguen esas familias que los amen.
Tordel, Juan Nieves y Ziggy sueñan con tener su hogar en esta Navidad
Ellos son parte del segmento Busco un hogar de EL UNIVERSO, el cual promueve la adopción y en su edición especial de diciembre recordamos sus historias.
Tortilla
Es una perrita hembra de 4 años que fue rescatada junto con sus nueve bebés en la laguna de Busa, en Azuay. Fue encontrada en estado famélico, pues fue abandonada cuando era una cachorra, según el hogar de acogida Salvavidas Cuenca, que se encargó de ayudarla.
“Pudimos llegar a su rescate y ahora ella lleva tres años a la espera de enamorar a una linda familia”, expresó la organización.
Tortilla está vacunada, esterilizada y desparasitada. Es de tamaño mediano. El proceso de adopción de Salvavidas Cuenca implica enviar un video y ubicación del domicilio del solicitante, además de una entrevista con el candidato adoptante y una visita al hogar, antes de finalizar el proceso.
Los aspirantes también deben comprometerse a seguir con el esquema regular de vacunas y a darle una vida plena y de calidad.
Puede adoptar a la cuenta de Instagram del hogar de acogida Salvavidas (@salvavidas_cuenca) o al siguiente número telefónico: 093-990-7966.
Alegría y sus chiquitos
Alegría es una perrita de aproximadamente ocho meses que estaba acostada en la vereda de una calle del sur de Guayaquil respirando lento y asustada.
La mascota estaba muy delgada y embarazada. La ayuda que necesitaba era urgente, dice refugio Pana: “Es imposible ver animales en condiciones deplorables y no detenerse para salvarlos. No podemos hacernos los ciegos, ser indiferentes con el dolor de esta pequeña”.
Escapulito, Cometa y Panchito están listos para una segunda oportunidad
Llevaron a Alegría a una veterinaria de confianza, donde se le realizaron los exámenes pertinentes: “Estaba anémica, desnutrición crónica y problemas en su piel producto del embarazo y baja de defensas. Descartaron que sea causada por ácaros”.
Alegría tenía mucho dolor en la barriga y, al siguiente día de ser rescatada, dio a luz a seis cachorritos: cinco machos y una hembra: Feliz, Pablo, Hitler, Amable, Antonio y Alma. Todos buscan un hogar.
Si deseas adoptar a Alegría o algunos de sus cachorros, puedes comunicarte con la fundación Refugio Pana a través del correo electrónico o a la cuenta de Instagram @fundacionrefugiopana.
